radiographic_examinations.findings: Distended gallbladder without pericholecystic fluid or gallbladder wall edema; tiny hypodensities in both kidneys; bibasilar atelectasis; fat-containing umbilical hernia; bilateral fat-containing inguinal hernias; grade 1 anterolisthesis of L5 on S1; otherwise normal findings in the liver, spleen, adrenal glands, pancreas, bowel loops, and bladder.
